{"word":"καταρρέω","slug":"καταρρέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>καταρρέω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>-ρεύσομαι</el>) (<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>-ρυήσομαι</el>) (<a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <el>-ερρύηκα</el>) (aor2 <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <el>-ερρύην</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to flow down</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, attic<p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of men, <i>to stream</i> or <i>rush down</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b>of fruit, leaves, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>, <i>to fall off</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>4. </b><i>to fall in ruins</i>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>5. </b><el>κ. εἴς τινα</el> <i>to come to, fall to the lot of</i>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b>, <b>Bion.</b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><el>κ. φόνῳ</el> <i>to run down with</i> blood, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; so in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}